packageJSON.name: menubar
packageJSON.description: high level way to create menubar desktop applications with atom-shell

releases.body:
Hello,

We've a live release with following changes.

Features:
- AR realtime availability status shown in UI
- Design changes on top banner.
- 'BookTime' user status changed to 'Learning'
- If user ends the conference, they may think they're going to disconnect from 3 legs, so we're going to convey by tooltip saying 'leave conference'

Bug Fixes:
- After leaving the conference line, V2 stuck in Busy rather going Available - fixed

**_Functionalities**_
1. Accounts will load faster than before. We are avoiding calls for Normal Forms when there is no Normal Message From configured and avoiding calls for Exportable Form when there is no Exportable Message Form Configured. So it will remove an RPC call to Job System application,
1. Filter message ( Date Filter ) based on Account Time zone,
2. Message Save and Send Type ID should be unique ( Save - c3cca2f9-9449-4c1a-80a4-2343f9e147a6 and Send - 523f3110-38e1-4302-86a2-df45f5f8621d ),
3. Code optimization for Lex and Synclio AnswerPhrase branding,
4. Enabled CSV mail format for Exportable Message Forms,
5. Requests has been requeued if message fail to persist in Full History,
6. Client Feedback UI experience and bug fixes,
7. Messages will be fetched using combination of Account Number and Unique Pin. So to avoid messages which are not related to new customer who signed up with the existing Account Number from the source pool,
8. Avoiding Exception Mails in case of IO, Socket Timeout, etc., if the request is handled by requeueing,
9. Added new Team VC page and
10. Changed Ajax ready state from 1 to 2. With the confirmation of state 1, connection has been established but some time request failed to reach server. With state 2, it confirms the request has been reached to server, which will avoid message loss and other services.

**_Bug Fix**_
1. If the Name field left empty and moving the focus to Phone field, if we type numbers in Phone field, it jumps back to Name field,
2. Current tab index change for Distributed Source and LoopToDo,
3. Thumbs Up and Thumbs Down LoopToDo change based on application environment ( Live or Staging ),
4.  API Key's for User Action Tracker and Transfer Board service to persist interactions in FULL History and

Analytics bug fixes.

releases.name: Test Release
releases.body:
IT,

We have moved a build to live with the following items, can you guys let us know if any report any kinda issue.

<title>Title of the document</title>

# Features

--> Notes ( Scratchpad ) - Changed the design for the notes and made it in a way that it will be available on load of the interactions right on top of the scripts ( Message Forms ),

--> Messages in the message history has been ordered based on the call answered time ( previously it was based on persisted time ),

 --> Creating task in Distributed Source if there is any configuration issue in the delivery method and/or contact methods which will reach to account management team based on brand,

--> Client service transfer line for UK accounts has been added in the call transfer option,

--> Account sign up date will be shown in account information if the account is signed up in the last 30 days, the idea is to convey associates give some high priority for those calls,

--> Message status tracker tool to identify if any message failed to Save and/or Send and

--> Accessing static map api service using APIKey. We were using this service to show location of the caller based on the phone number in the mail template.

# Application Information

App ID : alpha-sb
Version : notesdesign
Previous version : negativefeedback

# Git Info

test url : www.google.com

**\* Kamesh Header ***

It's very easy to make some words **bold** and other words _italic_ with Markdown. You can even [link to Google!](http://google.com)
http://www.gmail.com
http://www.facebook.com

Sometimes you want numbered lists:
1. One
2. Two
3. Three

Sometimes you want bullet points:
- Start a line with a star
- Profit!

Alternatively,
- Dashes work just as well
- And if you have sub points, put two spaces before the dash or star:
  - Like this
  - And this

If you want to embed images, this is how you do it:

![Image of Yaktocat](https://octodex.github.com/images/yaktocat.png)

# Structured documents

Sometimes it's useful to have different levels of headings to structure your documents. Start lines with a `#` to create headings. Multiple `##` in a row denote smaller heading sizes.

### This is a third-tier heading

You can use one `#` all the way up to `######` six for different heading sizes.

If you'd like to quote someone, use the > character before the line:

> Coffee. The finest organic suspension ever devised... I beat the Borg with it.
> - Captain Janeway

There are many different ways to style code with GitHub's markdown. If you have inline code blocks, wrap them in backticks: `var example = true`.  If you've got a longer block of code, you can indent with four spaces:

```
if (isAwesome){
  return true
}
```

GitHub also supports something called code fencing, which allows for multiple lines without indentation:

```
if (isAwesome){
  return true
}
```

And if you'd like to use syntax highlighting, include the language:

``` javascript
if (isAwesome){
  return true
}
```

# Functionalities
1.  Accounts will load faster than before. We are avoiding calls for Normal Forms when there is no Normal Message From configured and avoiding calls for Exportable Form when there is no Exportable Message Form Configured. So it will remove an RPC call to Job System application,
2.  Filter message ( Date Filter ) based on Account Time zone,
3.  Message Save and Send Type ID should be unique ( Save - c3cca2f9-9449-4c1a-80a4-2343f9e147a6 and Send - 523f3110-38e1-4302-86a2-df45f5f8621d ),
4.  Code optimization for Lex and Synclio AnswerPhrase branding,
5.  Enabled CSV mail format for Exportable Message Forms,
6.  Requests has been requeued if message fail to persist in Full History,
7.  Client Feedback UI experience and bug fixes,
8.  Messages will be fetched using combination of Account Number and Unique Pin. So to avoid messages which are not related to new customer who signed up with the existing Account Number from the source pool,
9.  Avoiding Exception Mails in case of IO, Socket Timeout, etc., if the request is handled by requeueing,
10. Added new Team VC page and
11. Changed Ajax ready state from 1 to 2. With the confirmation of state 1, connection has been established but some time request failed to reach server. With state 2, it confirms the request has been reached to server, which will avoid message loss and other services.

# Bug Fix
1.  If the Name field left empty and moving the focus to Phone field, if we type numbers in Phone field, it jumps back to Name field,
2.  Current tab index change for Distributed Source and LoopToDo,
3.  Thumbs Up and Thumbs Down LoopToDo change based on application environment ( Live or Staging ),
4.  Changed API Key's for User Action Tracker and Transfer Board service to persist interactions in FULL History and
5.  Analytics bug fixes.

**Implementation**
- FileDownloader for chat with electron  dialog api.
- Getting maximum tab loaded by user in SwitchBoard window and sending it analytics. 

**Bug Fix**
- Avoiding multiple download in engine Updation.
